    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-08-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="256"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d256">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Portman</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-08-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 31, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have received your several despatches numbered
                    and dated as follows: Nos. 29 and 30, June 1; No. 31, June 8; No. 32, June 9;
                    No. 33 and No. 34, June 10.</p>
                <p>The removal of the legation residence to Yedo is a gratifying circumstance, and
                    it is hoped that the new building intended for the use of our minister there,
                    which is now in course of preparation, may soon be completed.</p>
                <p>The intelligence which you have communicated in your No. 32, relative to the
                    Tycoon’s imposing demonstration for the suppression of the rebellion of Prince
                    Choshu, is very interesting, and it is sincerely hoped that the movement will
                    speedily result in a satisfactory solution of the difficulties which now beset
                    the empire. * * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. L. C. Portman,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., Yedo.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
